<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by NightGod on 02-01-2002 12:57 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I never charge for rezzes. I do accept 95% of the donations people offer (45+ only, below that, they have better things to do with their cash unless they're an obvious twink). If someone offers cash in an ooc or tell, I expect it. Yes, there are times I only go out of my way to do that rez because compensation was offered. There are other times no amount of cash will get me to move from where I am at. I turned down a couple donations yesterday because I was solo camping a quest spawn and was in a good mood. Plus, the people the rezzies were with gave me (combined) Koadic's, Storm Str, Mask of the Predator, Regrowth, SoW and CoE. Like hell I was gonna take their money after that-the whole point of a donation (IMHO) is a show of respect from that person that you did something you didn't have any obligation to do to make their life easier-mana can show that respect as easily as money can. Hell-most of the time I'm happy with them at least saying thank you and not just looting their corpse and running off without a word. I did accept a donation from someone else later in the day though, because I was grouped at the time. I also propmtly hit /s 62 after I hit trade. I always do so when grouped-the group's time is as valuable as mine. Outside of that, it really depends on my mood on accepting donations. I usually do because I have had a couple of people I turned down suddenly make me their main source when they need a rez. Run-bys, I'm usually gone before the person has zoned.

OK-starting to ramble...

